block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This updated version of The Events Calendar Pro includes a bug fix.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend updating on a <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">staging site</a>, just to be safe, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>When the option <strong>Calendar</strong> <strong>Manager</strong> was selected in <strong>Events</strong> &gt; <strong>Settings</strong> &gt; <strong>General</strong>, Event Tickets users could not access the attendees and orders pages and would see a permissions error instead. This has been fixed.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>0 new strings added</li><li>0 updated</li><li>0 fuzzied</li><li>0 obsoleted</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/the-events-calendar-pro-5-9-2-1/\">The Events Calendar Pro 5.9.2.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"3 Reasons Why Eventbrite and WordPress are the Perfect Pair\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:112:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/3-reasons-why-eventbrite-and-wordpress-are-the-perfect-pair/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 14 Oct 2021 11:18:43 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2318951\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:644:\"<p>Peanut butter and jelly. Spaghetti and meatballs. Pineapple and pizza. Okay so we may not know everything about perfect food pairings, but one thing we do know is that Eventbrite and WordPress are a match made in virtual event heaven. Why is that? Well, each brings a set of unique features and when they’re put&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/3-reasons-why-eventbrite-and-wordpress-are-the-perfect-pair/\">3 Reasons Why Eventbrite and WordPress are the Perfect Pair</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Jaime\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4320:\"\n<p>Peanut butter and jelly. Spaghetti and meatballs. Pineapple and pizza. Okay so we may not know everything about perfect food pairings, but one thing we do know is that Eventbrite and WordPress are a match made in virtual event heaven.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Why is that? Well, each brings a set of unique features and when they’re put together, they create the perfect combination. By adding <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Eventbrite</a> events directly to your WordPress site, you get the best of both worlds, letting Eventbrite handle some of the behind-the-scenes work while keeping users engaged on your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below we’ll elaborate on why these two are in it together for the long haul.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-1-increase-ticket-sales\">1. Increase ticket sales</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress is the perfect place to host your Eventbrite events. By <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/sell-eventbrite-tickets-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">adding your ticketed events</a> directly to your site, you can manage all of your Eventbrite ticket payments right from the WordPress dashboard, while keeping your users on your website throughout the ticket-buying process. This simplified approach can assist in the reduction of cart abandonment by preventing customers from leaving your site to purchase event tickets.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-2-keep-users-distraction-free\">2. Keep users distraction-free&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We all know that <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/virtual-event-burnout/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">virtual event fatigue</a> is real these days. There are so many online events to choose from, so how do you keep users coming to your event? By directing people to your Eventbrite events on your WordPress site, you can avoid user diversion to other events. This way, they’ll only see what <em>you</em> have to offer. Bonus points for adding related content to your event pages, so that you can even get some repeat customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-3-maintain-consistent-branding-and-styles\">3. Maintain consistent branding and styles</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Eventbrite is really good at taking care of payment information for your ticket sales. But there aren’t many styling options for events that live on the Eventbrite website. Instead, you can <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-add-an-eventbrite-widget-to-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">add your events</a> directly to your WordPress site so that you have flexibility in how you choose to style your events. You can easily choose a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WordPress theme</a> to reflect your style and branding choices. Without any extra work on your part, all of your events will match your website styles, creating an enhanced experience for your customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-take-things-to-the-next-level\">Take things to the next level&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As you’ve seen, Eventbrite and WordPress work in tandem to create a smooth workflow for you and your event attendees. Streamline the process even further with our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-eventbrite-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Eventbrite Tickets</a> plugin. With Eventbrite Tickets, create Eventbrite tickets and events right from the WordPress dashboard, automate event imports from your Eventbrite account, and manage ticket payments directly on WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>See Eventbrite Tickets in action on our <a href=\"https://demo.theeventscalendar.com/event/eventbrite-tickets-demo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">demo site</a> or request a demo to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/demo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">try things out</a> for yourself <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/3-reasons-why-eventbrite-and-wordpress-are-the-perfect-pair/\">3 Reasons Why Eventbrite and WordPress are the Perfect Pair</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"The Events Calendar 5.9.2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-eve